                    "company": "Faculdade de Ci\u00eancias da Universidade de Lisboa",
                    "description": "Ph.D. student at Faculdade de Ci\u00eancias da Universidade de Lisboa, in the BioPhysNano group of BioISI - Biosystems and Integrative Sciences Institute. During this period I focused on developing the Force Feedback Microscopy technique and tailor it to the analysis of biological systems. It included the project and commissioning of the new instrument, from the mechanical, optical and electrical perspectives together with its optimization and analysis from an engineering point-of-view. I performed multiple experiments involving biological systems, nanofluidics, nanofriction, and other nanoscale interactions, which further developed my experimental physics and data analysis capabilities.\nSeveral scientific publications came out from this work (most importantly found in doi.org/10.1038/s41598-017-03999-w and doi.org/10.1038/s41598-018-32021-0) and I participated in two international conferences (nanoPT2018 and ISMC2019) exposing my work. \nFollowing my passion for science outreach, I participated and organized multiple initiatives, including the creation and organization of a Ph.D. student conference of the Department of Physics of my university. I participated in several outreach activities directed to non-experts with all sorts of academic backgrounds: primary school, middle school, and high school students, Physics undergraduates and the general public.",
